snippet: The Federal Reserve’s Beige Book survey said falling oil prices and a strong dollar held back some sectors in January and February.
abstract: Federal Reserve's Beige Book survey finds economy growing in most of country in January and February, aided by rising consumer spending and home sales.
lead_paragraph: The Federal Reserve’s Beige Book survey said falling oil prices and a strong dollar held back some sectors in January and February.

headline.main: Fed Reports Economy Expanded in Most of U.S.
headline.print_headline: Fed Report Shows U.S. Economy Gaining Strength
